			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Denitration Agent</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">脱硝剂</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Desulfurizing Agent; Deoxidizing Agent; Calcium-based Ultrafine Powder</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Desulfurizing Agent; Deoxidizing Agent; Calcium-based Ultrafine Powder</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Other materials</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Denitration agents are substances used to reduce nitrogen oxides (NOx) emissions in various combustion processes. Unlike Selective Non-Catalytic Reduction (SNCR) that requires ammonia or other external agents, some denitration technologies do not need such additives, avoiding issues like ammonia escape and energy consumption for agent production. Denitration agents can come in various forms, including desulfurizing agents, deoxidizing agents, and calcium-based ultrafine powders. They are applied in different furnaces to control emissions and are part of a market that is expected to grow in the coming years.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">脱硝剂是用于减少各种燃烧过程中氮氧化物（NOx）排放的物质。与需要氨或其他外部制剂的选择性非催化还原（SNCR）不同，一些脱硝技术不需要此类添加剂，避免了氨逃逸和制剂生产能耗等问题。脱硝剂可以有多种形式，包括脱硫剂、脱氧剂和钙基超细粉末。它们被应用于不同的熔炉以控制排放，是未来几年预计将增长的市场的一部分。</common:generalComment>
